data.title: Struggling but not bad
data.text: I am a Taco snob!  Yxtlan provide all the dishes required for a Mexican experience but it lacks the authenticity one expects from a Taqueria in the middle of a barrio.  They seem to be trying to provide an American experience instead of just cooking the way they do in the home.  Close and in an active strip mall with many other places to eat.

data.title: Probably not again
data.text:
The place just didn't do it for me.  The initial offering of chips and salsa was some of the worst I've ever had.  Really.  The chips tasted not only days old, but deep fried a few too many times..  The salsa, or hot sauce was of the watery red variety.  This was unacceptable.

Dishes we tried included a variety of tacos that were fair but not overwhelmingly good.  Beans were ok, but the rice was again old.  

Service was good, as he obliged our request for a significantly better salsa to try, and he offered a sample of a variety of meat called tinga that we had not experienced before.  The bottled soda that we ordered was really big, and great value for the price.

All in all, I probably wouldn't go back, although I did like the feel of the out of way, dusty road feel to the area.

data.title: Best Tacos Ever!
data.text:
Get the tacos de lengua and the tacos de cabeza, and get a horchata to wash it down.

I am going back there very soon, see you there!
